<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>3632</id>
    <title>Site Settings: Selecting new blog language changes the names of the languages in the Language list</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">1 Select a site and open the Settings</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">2 Select Language (to choose the blog language)</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">Note that the list of languages displays the name of each language in that language and below displays the name of each language in your language (e.g. English/English, Deutsch/German, Español/Spanish).</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.5">3 Select a new language from the list.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.6">Result: The second name of each language changes to the name of that language in the language you just selected (so if you select Español/Spanish, the list becomes e.g. English/Inglés, Deutsch/Alemán, Español/Español).</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">The blog language shouldn't affect the UI language, so the list of languages should always respect the device/app UI language and not the selected blog language.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Screenshot with English selected as the blog language:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
